Berlusconi Says Italy’s Fundamentals Solid, Bond Rout Due to Speculation

-- B y   J e f f r e y   D o n o v a n
-- 
2011-08-03T15:38:28Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-03/berlusconi-says-italy-s-fundamentals-solid-bond-rout-due-to-speculation.html
Prime Minister  Silvio Berlusconi  said
Italy has “solid” economic fundamentals and liquid banks, and
its bond-market rout is due to speculation and sagging
international confidence. He made his remarks today in an
address to the Chamber of Deputies in  Rome .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jeffrey Donovan at 
 jdonovan26@bloomberg.net  